com.paydiant.android.ui.service.account

Class PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.ui.service.account.PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPaymentAccountBalanceRefreshListener, IPaymentAccountManagementListener, IPaymentAccountManagementMetaDataListener, IProvisionAccountListener

    public class PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements IProvisionAccountListener
    Provides empty implementation for IPaymentAccountManagementListener and IPaymentAccountManagementMetaDataListener interfaces. Any classes that need to use a subset of the IPaymentAccountManagementListener or IPaymentAccountManagementMetaDataListener methods can utilize this adapter class by overriding the required methods. 

           PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter paymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter = new PaymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter() {
          @Override
          public void onPaymentAccountsRetrievalSuccess(List paymentAccountList) {
          }
          
          @Override
          public void onPaymentAccountRetrievalSuccess(PaymentAccountComplete paymentAccount) {
          }
      };
      iPaymentAccountManagementService.setPaymentAccountRetrieveListener(paymentAccountManagementListenerAdapter);
    Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.

    Paydiant
